gomodel:SYNGO_4934  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 7:\nmIPSCs amplitudes were similar in striatopallidal synapses of LAMP5 WT and KO mice while the frequency of mIPSCs in KO mice was increased, suggesting a change in the presynaptic release apparatus.\n\n\"As LAMP5 is specifically expressed in striatal terminals, presynaptic function of the GABAergic striatopallidal synapse was investigated by using short-term plasticity protocols. The results showed that paired-pulse ratios (PPRs) of IPSCs, a standard measure of neurotransmitter release probability, were strongly affected in LAMP5 KO mice. The moderate paired-pulse depression of striatopallidal synapses observed in WT mice was replaced by a strong facilitation in LAMP5 KO mice at all four interstimulus intervals (Fig 7C). This suggests that deletion of LAMP5 decreases release probability, the most common cause for paired-pulse facilitation. We then investigated the behavior of striatopallidal synapses during trains of stimuli at moderate frequency (10 pulses at 20 and 50 Hz). In these experiments synapses showed frequency-dependent short-term depression in WT mice (Fig 7D). Conversely, LAMP5-deficient mice exhibited a pronounced augmentation for the entire duration of the train, both at 20 and 50 Hz (Fig 7D).\"\n\nauthors conclude:\n\"Altogether, these results suggest that LAMP5 appears critical for the regulation of spontaneous vesicular release and the dynamics of evoked GABAergic transmission, especially during periods of moderate activity.\". Experimental description: \"LAMP5 conditional mutant mice were generated by the KO-KI Booster platform, CIPHE, Marseille...\" (p.2/19)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
